### Design Properties from Figma

#### 🎨 Color Styles

- Primary Color: #FF5A5F (Airbnb Red)
- Secondary Color: #484848 (Dark Gray Text)
- Accent Color: #00A699 (Teal)
- Background Color: #F7F7F7
- Card/Component Background: #FFFFFF
- Button Hover: #E51D28

#### 🅰️ Typography

- **Font Family**: Circular Std (or fallback: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif)
- **Font Weights**: Regular (400), Medium (500), Bold (700)
- **Font Sizes**:
  - Headings: 32px, 24px
  - Body Text: 16px, 14px
  - Captions: 12px

#### 🧠 Why Design Properties Matter

Identifying color styles and typography in a mockup is essential for design consistency and a cohesive user experience. These visual properties define the mood, tone, and readability of the interface. Sticking to a clear design system ensures that all developers and designers are aligned and able to scale the UI across pages and components effectively.
